## ITERATION 42A BODY

title: "042A — Correct Route-to-Marker Visual Anchoring"
description: "Fix the visual mismatch between the route origin and the enlarged vehicle marker so the route appears to begin at the marker center."

:::GOALS

Ensure the route visually appears to start from the center of the vehicle marker.

The current geographic start point is correct, but the enlarged custom marker is visually offset from that anchor because the rendered marker footprint is much larger than the default Leaflet anchor assumption.

:::END

:::TASKS

Do not change the route geometry logic further.

Keep the first route segment anchored to the vehicle latitude/longitude.

Instead, correct the visual anchoring by fixing the vehicle marker overlay anchoring.

Review the rendered vehicle marker positioning logic and ensure the marker is centered exactly on the vehicle's map point.

If the marker is positioned with CSS transforms or container offsets, ensure those offsets place the visual center of the marker at the map coordinate.

Specifically:

- the operational ring center must align to the vehicle lat/lng point
- the center marker body must align to the same point
- the directional arrow must remain centered within that structure

If needed, update the overlay positioning so the marker container is translated by half its rendered width and height.

Verify that the first route segment passes through the visual center of the marker, not the outer ring edge.

Preserve current route rendering, marker size, and marker hierarchy.

:::END

:::ACCEPTANCE

- The route start point remains the vehicle lat/lng.
- The vehicle marker is visually centered on that same point.
- The first route segment appears to originate from the center of the marker.
- The route no longer appears attached to the outer ring edge.

:::END